INSERT INTO spk_posts VALUES('99', '1', '2015-02-20 15:10:03', '2015-02-20 15:10:03', '<p>Kamilla takes satisfaction in creating a peace of mind to individuals and families by helping them protect their assets and prepare for significant life events.Â  Kamillaâs work product is distinguished by her analytical capabilities to think outside of the box in finding creative and innovative solutions to reduce clientsâ costs without bearing on quality and reliability. Kamillaâs experience as a business owner and lawyer makes her uniquely qualified to provide the practical advice that matters most to clients.</p>\n<p>Prior to entering law school, Kamilla acquired invaluable experience and skills working in real estate and as a small business owner.Â  During her first year of law school, Kamilla was in the top 2% of her class, and was awarded Highest Grade Honors in Legal Research &amp; Writing II, Criminal Law, Contracts II, and Property I.Â  While in law school, Kamilla assisted low-income residents with their tax returns through the Volunteer Income Tax Assistance (VITA) program, and externed for the Honorable Judith H. Wizmur, Bankruptcy Court for the District of New Jersey. Kamilla also interned for The Exoneration Initiative (EXI), where she investigated claims of wrongfully convicted persons in New York.</p>\n<p>After graduating from Rutgers School of Law â Camden, Kamilla served on the defense team for a high profile federal corruption case, and was associated with the law firm of Schonfeld &amp; Weinstein, LLP, a prominent Wall Street firm focusing on securities and estate planning.Â  Kamilla is the founding principal of Mishiyeva Law, where she specializes in finding creative solutions for clients in the areas of Estate Planning, Estate Litigation, Asset Protection, Probate, Trusts and Estate Administration, and Taxation.</p>\n<p>Kamilla is licensed to practice law in all New York State Courts, and the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York.Â  She is a member of the American Bar Association and the New York Bar Association.</p>\n<p><strong>Education</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Rutgers School of Law - Camden, J.D.</li>\n<li>Baruch College, B.A.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Bar Admission</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>New York State</li>\n<li>US District Court for the Southern District of New York</li>\n</ul>\n', 'Kamilla Mishiyeva, Esq.', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '45-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-02-20 15:10:03', '2015-02-20 15:10:03', '', '45', 'http://lawyertestsite.com/mishiyevalaw/45-autosave-v1/', '0', 'revision', '', '0');
